      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh my bad, forgot i hadn't uploaded it yet. here it is:\n\n\"4.2 Price Adjustments: During peak demand months (defined as June-August), the Supplier reserves the right to implement a price adjustment of up to 5% per month to account for market volatility. Such adjustments shall be applied automatically to the monthly billing cycle without requiring prior written notice or formal amendment to this Agreement.\"\n\nso based on that, are we safe from any sudden price jumps? i really need to confirm there's no way they can just raise the price on us without a signed agreement.",
